Note: Debug and Performance Monitoring Functions
Process called "create_syntax_debug_tracer" returns SyntaxDebugTracer:
    Return SyntaxDebugTracer with:
        trace_level as "info"
        trace_output as list containing
        syntax_events as list containing
        metadata as dictionary containing

Process called "create_syntax_performance_monitor" returns SyntaxPerformanceMonitor:
    Return SyntaxPerformanceMonitor with:
        metrics as dictionary containing
        thresholds as dictionary containing:
            "extension_registration_time" as 1.0
            "operator_registration_time" as 0.5
            "construct_registration_time" as 0.5
            "extension_parsing_time" as 1.0
            "operator_resolution_time" as 0.1
        alerts as list containing
        metadata as dictionary containing

Process called "get_syntax_trace" that takes extensions as SyntaxExtensions returns List[SyntaxTraceEntry]:
    Return extensions.debug_tracer.trace_output

Process called "get_syntax_events" that takes extensions as SyntaxExtensions returns List[SyntaxEvent]:
    Return extensions.debug_tracer.syntax_events

Process called "clear_syntax_trace" that takes extensions as SyntaxExtensions:
    Set extensions.debug_tracer.trace_output to list containing
    Set extensions.debug_tracer.syntax_events to list containing

Process called "get_syntax_performance_metrics" that takes extensions as SyntaxExtensions returns Dictionary[String, SyntaxPerformanceMetric]:
    Return extensions.performance_monitor.metrics

Process called "get_syntax_performance_alerts" that takes extensions as SyntaxExtensions returns List[SyntaxPerformanceAlert]:
    Return extensions.performance_monitor.alerts

Process called "set_syntax_performance_threshold" that takes extensions as SyntaxExtensions and metric as String and threshold as Float returns Boolean:
    Try:
        Set extensions.performance_monitor.thresholds[metric] to threshold
        Return true
        
    Catch error:
        Return false

Note: Result Types
Type ExtensionParseResult is:
    | ExtensionParseSuccess with ast as ASTNode and tokens as List[Token] and metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]
    | ExtensionParseError with error as String and details as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type OperatorResolutionResult is:
    | OperatorResolutionSuccess with result as Any and operator as CustomOperator and metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]
    | OperatorResolutionError with error as String and details as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type OperatorConflict is Dictionary with:
    conflict_id as String
    operator1 as CustomOperator
    operator2 as CustomOperator
    conflict_type as String
    resolution as String
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any] 